            . I am an officer. I went to the prisoner's lodgings, his wife and children were there; I found this iron behind the water-butt, wrapped up in a cloth; this piece was taken from an old iron shop in Whitecross-street. The prisoner said it was distress that made him do it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I wanted bread for my family.</p>
